title: Zucchini Pizza Casserole
directions: Place zucchini in strainer; sprinkle with salt. Let stand for 10 minutes. Squeeze out moisture.
Combine zucchini with the egg whites, parmesan, garlic powder, italian seasoning, and half of the mozzarella. Press into a greased 13×9-in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, cook turkey and dried minced onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Add marinara; spoon over zucchini mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; top with pepperoni. Bake 15- 20 minutes longer.
ingredients: 1-1/2 cups shredded part-skim mozzarella cheese, divided
